                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1"><desc>Three leaves are added in front of the manuscript. The first remained blank, while the two other ones are written on both sides. The writing on these pages is ugly and careless. The text on them is the well known morning prayer "Kidan zanageh (Compare Dillmann's Catalogue of the Ethiopic Manuscripts of the British Museum No.20 and others.) The volume belonged to a certain Honorius."</desc></item>
                            </list>
                        </additions>
